title: Express.js
content:
-framework for node.js
-it is defining the routes GET, POST, PUT.. etc. and handling incoming http requests
-managing request and response, creating API simpler

title: vayne

title: GET
content: Retrieves data from the server. For example, fetching a list of notes. GET requests are safe (they don’t modify any data) and can be cached.

title: POST
content: Sends data to the server to create a new resource. When you add a new note, you typically use a POST request. This method can change the state of the server (like adding new data).

title: PUT
content: Updates an existing resource by replacing it entirely. For instance, if you update a note’s title and content, you might use a PUT request. It’s usually used when you have a complete new version of the resource.

title: DELETE
content: Removes a resource from the server. When you delete a note, a DELETE request is sent to remove that note from the backend.
